    <briefdescription>
<para>GPU-accelerated operations for physics computations. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>The AnalysisG framework includes extensive CUDA support for accelerating computationally intensive physics operations. The CUDA modules are organized into namespaces that provide specific functionality.</para>
<sect1 id="group__cuda__group_1cuda_overview">
<title>Overview</title>
<para>The CUDA code is located in <computeroutput>src/AnalysisG/pyc/</computeroutput> and provides GPU-accelerated implementations of:</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Physics calculations (kinematics, invariant masses)</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Coordinate transformations</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><ref refid="classGraph" kindref="compound">Graph</ref> operations (aggregation, reconstruction)</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Neutrino reconstruction (NuSol algorithm)</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Mathematical operators (matrix operations, rotations)</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
</sect1>
<sect1 id="group__cuda__group_1cuda_namespaces">
<title>Namespaces</title>
<para><table rows="6" cols="3"><row>
<entry thead="yes"><para>Namespace   </para>
