<sect1 id="group__cuda__group_1cuda_integration">
<title>PyTorch Integration</title>
<para>All CUDA operations are integrated with PyTorch tensors, allowing seamless GPU acceleration within the ML pipeline. Functions accept <computeroutput>torch::Tensor*</computeroutput> arguments and return <computeroutput>torch::Tensor</computeroutput> results.</para>
<para>Example usage in C++: <programlisting filename=".cpp"><codeline><highlight class="preprocessor">#include<sp/>&lt;<ref refid="physics_8cuh" kindref="compound">physics/physics.cuh</ref>&gt;</highlight><highlight class="normal"></highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"></highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">torch::Tensor<sp/><ref refid="enums_8h_1a666fa98df084d96fc481369704153b28a04130da60e65c7800006cd7886515b56" kindref="member">pmc</ref><sp/>=<sp/>...;<sp/></highlight><highlight class="comment">//<sp/>[N,<sp/>4]<sp/>tensor<sp/>of<sp/>(px,<sp/>py,<sp/>pz,<sp/>E)</highlight><highlight class="normal"></highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">torch::Tensor<sp/><ref refid="enums_8h_1a666fa98df084d96fc481369704153b28ad90ccffa01275a7a7795fb6d1274e75f" kindref="member">mass</ref><sp/>=<sp/><ref refid="namespacephysics___1a64e8e583c57246f52851c0bff4137ebc" kindref="member">physics_::M</ref>(&amp;<ref refid="enums_8h_1a666fa98df084d96fc481369704153b28a04130da60e65c7800006cd7886515b56" kindref="member">pmc</ref>);</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">torch::Tensor<sp/>beta<sp/>=<sp/><ref refid="namespacephysics___1a3123f743b9c22850e7346d5f56a4441b" kindref="member">physics_::Beta</ref>(&amp;<ref refid="enums_8h_1a666fa98df084d96fc481369704153b28a04130da60e65c7800006cd7886515b56" kindref="member">pmc</ref>);</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting> </para>
</sect1>
